Edward Thomas Foulkes was an architect who was born in Monmouth, OR in 1874, and died in Oakland, CA in 1967. He was educated at Stanford University and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) before attending classes at the École des Beaux-Arts in Paris. Notable buildings he designed include the Pittock Mansion in Portland, OR, the Hotel Fresno, the Einstein House and the Brix house in Fresno, CA, and the buildings he designed for the Panama–Pacific International Exposition.
